a pair of worn faded overalls has caused 
a flap at city hall where the mayor wants a councilman to pay more 
attention to his appearance 
after councilman andrew jackson mcknight showed up recently at a 
city council workshop in overalls mayor david head issued a memo 
asking councilmen to dress properly when representing richwood a 
small town about 50 miles south of houston 
the memo mentions no names but head said it was directed at 
mcknight his memo does not ban jeans but asks that they be clean 
and in good shape 
while im sure that faded overalls and tshirts are 
comfortable i feel that they have no place in the council 
chambers head wrote 
hell will freeze over before i let anyone tell me how to 
dress mcknight said its nobodys business how a person 
dresses if someone wants to come down there in rags thats his 
business 
he intends to wear his overalls to the july 11 council meeting 
mcknight 54 said he has only worn overalls once since being 
elected in may and that was because he didnt have time to change 
after taking care of some goats at his farm 
but head said mcknight has shown up at city hall wearing tshirts 
with holes around the neck and cares little about his appearance 
when representing the city 
mcknight lost an election to head in 1988 but won a council post 
by a slim margin as a writein candidate in may head 50 stepped 
down from his council post to run unopposed for mayor in may 
