the move in the senate came as several lawmakers introduced 
constitutional amendments in the house following the supreme court 
decision house speaker thomas s foley dwash said such attempts 
should be taken cautiously and that it would be extraordinarily 
slow to amend the first amendment to the constitution which is 
at the heart of our constitutional liberties and freedom 
biden said his simple legislation could accomplish the same aim 
as a constitutional amendment 
the bill reads whoever knowingly and publicly mutilates 
defaces burns displays on the floor or ground or tramples upon 
any flag of the united states shall be fined not more than 1000 or 
imprisoned for not more than one year or both 
bidens bill is identical to the federal statute on flag 
desecration except it removes the words cast contempt 
the majority supreme court opinion reasoned that a texas statute 
on flag desecration violated the first amendment because it was 
aimed at protecting against acts toward the flag which would be 
offensive to others bidens measure would treat desecration as an 
act of vandalism without considering whether anyone was offended by 
the act presumably answering the courts first amendment concerns 
the house may consider next week a resolution similar to the one 
passed by the senate this week expressing opposition to the view of 
the court 
