cardinal timothy manning a champion of the 
poor and oppressed during his 15 years as roman catholic archbishop 
of los angeles has died of spinal cancer at 79 
he died friday at the norris cancer hospital of the university of 
southern california said aj antczak managing editor of the 
tidings the diocesan newspaper 
mannings successor archbishop roger mahony was at mannings 
side when he died we were praying the litany of saints when he 
peacefully slipped away mahony said 
mahony who compared mannings life to that of father junipero 
serra the 18th century priest who founded the missions in 
california said it was as if we were just adding his name to that 
long list of heroic and saintly men and women to whom we commended 
his spirit 
a native of ireland manning arrived in the united states in 
1928 although he retired as archbishop in 1985 he observed the 
55th anniversary of his ordination as a priest on friday antczak 
said 
manning was a man of great strength courage and compassion 
former president reagan said in a statement he enriched the life 
of thousands who are better because of his good work 
mayor tom bradley ordered flags at city buildings flown at 
halfstaff in mannings honor 
manning after serving two years as a bishop in fresno became 
archbishop in 1970 taking over from cardinal james francis 
mcintyre whose final years in los angeles were filled with discord 
in 1970 minority catholics complained of alienation weekly 
during protests in front of st basils catholic church 
young priests and nuns often found themselves at odds with the 
hierarchy and quietly referred to the chancery as the fortress 
manning moved his residence to st vibianas church in the skid 
row section of los angeles he established ministries for blacks and 
hispanics and began a priests senate to give the clergy greater 
say an interparochial council extended the participation to the 
parish level 
manning also visited with local protestant and jewish 
congregations 
he assured vietnam war protesters they could declare themselves 
conscientious objectors and often spoke against the nuclear arms 
race saying in 1981 the cry of the poor for bread has been 
answered by warheads 
in 1983 he petitioned then secretary of state george shultz to 
halt the deportation of salvadoran refugees 
his social liberalism was matched by a theological conservatism 
he denounced abortion as murder and announced that any catholic who 
cooperated in an abortion would be excommunicated from the church 
bishop john ward who served as mannings auxiliary bishop said 
of manning he was an outstanding princely gentleman the perfect 
priest who was devoted to his work with priests and people alike 
after ordination in 1934 he went to rome for postgraduate 
studies at the gregorian institute in rome he received a doctor of 
canon law degree in 1938 
he was named an auxiliary bishop in 1946 and consecrated a full 
bishop the same year two years later he was made chancellor in los 
angeles and in 1955 he was made vicar general in 1967 he was 
appointed bishop of fresno 
in 1973 pope paul vi elevated manning to the college of 
cardinals 
a mass of christian burial will be celebrated wednesday morning 
and throughout the day his remains will lie in state 
more than 100 bishops from around the globe were expected to 
gather thursday morning for another mass of christian burial and 
burial will follow 
