northern slovenia is the nations most developed and most liberal 
republic the republics communist leadership advocates regional 
autonomy closer ties with the west and has indicated an openness to 
democratic elections 
the democratic union is the first of several political 
associations that have been formally constituted in slovenia 
slovenian liberalism has been viewed with misgivings by communist 
leaders in the countrys other republics particualarly in serbia 
yugoslavias government center there orthodox communists oppose 
reforms as a step toward restoration of the westernstyle democracy 
that yugoslavia had before the war favoring greater central control 
